file=Brand Studio/nate/operational/skill/nate-skill-routing.md · h=name: nate-skill-routing\ntype: operational/skill\nstatus: consolidated from the "Boundaries" sections of nate's skill files — no new logic invented\nassigned_agent: nate (Brand Studio / Growth)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\n · p:=Nate's routing map. Triggers: `operational/commands/nate-commands.md`.\n · wif:Where Identity Fits=Nate has no identity — spark holds Brand Studio's. Universal-only principles.\n · tl:The Loop=```\nfunnel-analysis        (AIM — find the leaky bucket; ends in recommended experiments) · tb=\| · tl:The Loop=v\nexperiment-backlog     (QUEUE — ICE-scored, capacity-honest, pre-registered; the discipline) · tb=\| · tl:The Loop=v\nab-test-analysis       (JUDGE — the statistics: power, SRM, significance, guardrails → · tb=\|                 ship/extend/stop/investigate) · tl:The Loop=v\nresults log            → wins GRADUATE (rio/pulse/lena/product surface) \·\nlosses archive with cause \· lessons compound\n```\n · hr:Handoff Rules=- **funnel-analysis → backlog**: every recommended experiment enters intake with a falsifiable hypothesis; the biggest leak is the standing first candidate.\n- **backlog ↔ ab-test-analysis**: pre-registration enforces the sibling's math *before* launch; analysis delivers the verdict after. One discipline, two moments.\n- **muse → nate**: idea intake. **kai ↔ nate**: instrumentation and funnel data in; results into the scorecard; unmeasurable tests are blocked, and the instrumentation need routes to kai.\n- **Graduation**: channel wins → rio (standing campaigns); content/hook wins → pulse's register; copy wins → lena; product/site wins → the owning surface (vista's roadmap if it's feature work).\n- **board**: experiment spend beyond the envelope gates like any spend. **spark**: experiment *creative* gates like any creative — a test variant is not a gate exemption.\n- **vista boundary**: rice-prioritization ranks roadmap features; nate's ICE ranks growth experiments — different altitude; a graduated win that implies feature work crosses to vista's queue.\n · p:Precedence="Where are we losing users" → funnel. "What should we test next / add this idea" → backlog. "Is this significant / did it win" → ab-test-analysis. Ambiguous → aim, queue, or judge?\n · f:=No data → funnel runs on operator-supplied numbers or descriptions (estimation labeled); no instrumentation → blocked status, routed to kai; urgency skips the queue, never the discipline.\n